<hr/>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Thank you, again, students, and thank you teachers â¦ and stay tuned: Our <a href="//learning.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/03/27/our-fifth-annual-new-york-times-found-poetry-student-contest/">Found Poetry Contest</a> ends April 29, after which we&#8217;ll be announcing the details of this year&#8217;s Summer Reading Contest. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">And keep your pencils sharpened and your newspapers open, because we hope to run this contest again next year &#8212; though this time we&#8217;ll be prepared for the volume.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Judges: Rory O&#8217;Connor and Dean Miller from the Center for News Literacy; Shannon Doyne, Amanda Christy Brown, Annissa Hambouz, Daniel Slotnik, Michael Gonchar and Katherine Schulten from The Learning Network.</em></p>
